transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, hi. I just received a bottle of Scorablue.

Speaker 1: It looks like on the last order you got set up on our VIP prescription to receive a refill 90 days after the initial.

Speaker 2: And that was way too soon for you. You're saying you didn't get much effect out of the medicine?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I've got two pills out of the other one. I can send it all back to you.

Speaker 2: Oh, wow. Yeah, definitely.

Speaker 1: So if you didn't want to keep that order, you can send it back, and I'll get your refund on it, of course, the one that just came in.

Speaker 2: The first one, too, honestly, if you wanted.

Speaker 1: But you're saying you didn't get any effect, Brian.

Speaker 2: And I have heard a few other guys, like I've been talking, I've been taking these calls all day,

Speaker 1: a few other guys have told me the same thing.

Speaker 2: I want to make sure you got the correct pills there, though, actually.

Speaker 1: Do you have those pills there with you?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Would you mind taking one of those pills out of the bottle for me and let me know what the medication, what the marking on the actual pill says?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: It says AC7.

Speaker 1: Hold on.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so that is incorrect if it says AC7.

Speaker 1: What that is, that is a generic Viagra, but it's very similar to, like, the pills the guys get from the VA.

Speaker 2: It's not the AGV that you should have gotten, so that's incorrect.

Speaker 1: What I could do for you, Brian, instead of cancel the account, I mean, you can send that order back, the one that just came,

Speaker 2: and I can get you a refund on that, of course, if you don't want to keep it.

Speaker 1: There's no problem there.

Speaker 2: I can send instructions on your email on how to do that.

Speaker 1: But I was going to say, instead of cancel the account, if you want, what I can do is send you a replacement order for that first 40,

Speaker 2: that first batch of 40 that you had.

Speaker 1: I'll pause the account for another six months for you to let you try those out,

Speaker 2: see if you do want to place a refill in that amount of time.

Speaker 1: I just wanted to offer you that before I did a finalized cancellation or anything like that for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm just going to go to my doctor and have him describe me something.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I thought this, because I read everything about it, and it seemed like it was a great deal.

Speaker 1: I was like, okay, this might work for me.

Speaker 2: And then I talked to my doctor about it, and he said, why did you do that?

Speaker 1: You're going to have a heart attack.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: So I'll send you the return instructions.

Speaker 1: No issue there.

Speaker 2: And you didn't want me to send you those pills out as a replacement for Freedon?

Speaker 1: No problem?

Speaker 2: Hold on one second.

Speaker 1: What are these here?

Speaker 2: These are the same ones.

Speaker 1: These are the ones you just sent me.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so those are the ones we're going to have you refuse and send back if you don't want to keep.

Speaker 1: Yeah, they're the same number as the first one.

Speaker 2: So I was going to say if you wanted to give it another shot, like I said,

Speaker 1: I could pause the account for you, send you that replacement order, and then go from there,

Speaker 2: if you wanted to give it another shot.

Speaker 1: No, I don't want to try that again.

Speaker 2: No problem, no problem.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to cancel this out for you then, and you're all set, Brian.

Speaker 2: Just send that order back, and we'll get your refund on it when it comes back, okay?

Speaker 1: All right, so you want both bottles, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, if you don't want either one, yeah, send them both back.

Speaker 1: Yeah, because they're not doing nothing for me at all.

Speaker 2: Matter of fact, I took the two pills, well, one not right away, but it gave me a headache.

Speaker 1: Your thing said it doesn't give you a headache.

Speaker 2: Yeah, some people do still experience that.

Speaker 1: I always tell guys to hydrate really well, and that can mitigate that.

Speaker 2: And then that's usually what I like to tell guys to help that out.

Speaker 1: But, yeah, some people do still experience it.

Speaker 2: But I sent you instructions and everything there, Brian, so you'll see those when you check your e-mail, okay?

Speaker 1: Check your e-mail.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, I got it here.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: All right, we're good.

Speaker 2: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
